<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06053l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06053l">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06053l"> 53(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> little man in&apos;s eye / (pupil)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La v&eacute;rit&eacute; est que les Romains donnaient aux petites filles le nom de <i>pupa</i> (diminutif <i>pupula</i> et <i>pupilla</i>, d&apos;o&ugrave; le mot fran&ccedil;ais <i>pupille</i>, dans ses deux acceptions: <i>fille mineure</i> et <i>pupille de l&apos;oil</i>, ainsi appel&eacute;e &agrave; cause de <mark>la petite figure qu&apos;on voit se refl&eacute;ter dans la prunelle</mark>). <font color="green">[The truth is that the Romans gave the little girls the name pupa (diminutive pupula and pupilla, hence the French word pupil, in its two meanings: minor daughter and pupil of the eye, so called because of the small figure which one sees reflected in the pupil).]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 117</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01124a" href="c01all.htm#c01124a">VI.C.01:124(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
